text: Heat index values up to 109 are possible in Central & North Texas. A Heat Advisory is in effect for Milam County through 8 pm Friday. AUSTIN, TX â€” New details are revealed regarding the investigation into the arrest of a Southwest Austin massage parlor owner on allegations of human trafficking. This happened at RS Foot Massage on Highway 290 in the Oak Hill area. ALSO| Austin massage parlor owner arrested on charges of human trafficking A search warrant says Austin police searched the business and found documents showing felony charges, address books, ledgers, tally books, and financial documents. Officers found evidence relating to the obtaining, transferring, and concealment of prostitution funds. Police also found telephone recording equipment, condoms, and personal identification documents including passports and driver's licenses. Court documents say commercial sex advertisements were linked to the business' phone number. These ads were posted to adultsearch.com and featured pictures of Asian females. We're also learning that the Austin Police Department interviewed two men who were seen leaving the business. One had been to RS Foot Massage six times and received sex acts during the massages. The second man says he went to the massage parlor three times and agreed to masturbation each time. This is still an ongoing investigation.
